
@startuml
class Student {
  - studentID: String
  - name: String
  + requestAppointment(course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  - taID: String
  - name: String
  - coursesTaught: List<Course>
  + scheduleAppointment(student: Student, course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class Course {
  - courseID: String
  - name: String
  - teachingAssistants: List<TeachingAssistant>
}

class Appointment {
  - appointmentID: String
  - date: Date
  - time: Time
  - student: Student
  - teachingAssistant: TeachingAssistant
  - course: Course
}

Student "1" -- "many" Course : registeredFor
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "many" Course : teaches
Course "1" -- "many" Appointment : has
Student "1" -- "1" Appointment : requests
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "1" Appointment : provides
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **Student** can be registered for multiple **Courses**.
- A **Teaching Assistant** can teach multiple **Courses**.
- Each **Appointment** is associated with one **Student**, one **Teaching Assistant**, and one **Course**.
- A **Student** can only request an appointment for a **Course** they are registered for.
- A **Teaching Assistant** can only provide help for the **Courses** they are teaching.

